title: "pet-doi-ml: Machine Learning for Depth-of-Interaction Calibration in PET Imaging"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-03-02"
url: "https://github.com/aupbrown/ml-doi-calibration"
license: MIT
authors:
  - family-names: Brown
    given-names: Austin
    affiliation: "Radiation Imaging Laboratory, University of Arizona"
keywords:
  - PET
  - depth-of-interaction
  - DOI
  - CZT
  - RENA-3
  - machine learning
  - medical imaging
  - nuclear instrumentation
abstract: >
  A pipeline for training machine learning models to estimate Depth-of-Interaction (DOI)
  in CZT-based PET detectors. Features are extracted from raw CAEN digitizer waveforms
  by emulating the RENA-3 ASIC signal processing chain (RC-CR pulse shaping, leading-edge
  trigger, peak amplitude extraction), enabling models trained on Arizona collimator-scan
  data to be deployed on Stanford RENA-3 PET systems without retraining.
